description:
Breaking Glass Pictures is proud to release the coming-of-age LGBTQ drama On the Fringe of Wild.

Early 2000s. A small, northern Ontario town. Canada. Peter, a sensitive and shy teen, dreams of leaving his small northern Ontario town to pursue life as an artist, but his homophobic father intends to 'make him a man' instead. 

Forcing him on a hunting trip one cold winter break, tensions run high and Peter runs away. Lost, cold and reaching his breaking point, Peter meets Jack, who's also desperate to escape his toxic family situation. A romance quickly develops between the two teenage boys as they hide away in a secluded cabin, discovering each other and themselves. But the world outside eventually pulls them back and they're forced to face the circumstances they tried to flee, which will ultimately tear them apart.

Available October 12, 2021

title: DIY Fringe Wig: Tools, Techniques, and Useful Tips | Beginner Friendly
description:
Welcome to Our Channel

Are you ready to embark on a journey of creative self-expression and master the art of wig-making? In this tutorial, we'll guide you through the process of crafting your very own fringe wig, complete with the essential tools, step-by-step techniques, and valuable tips to ensure your success.

Tools You'll Need:

Before we dive into the exciting world of fringe wig creation, let's familiarize ourselves with the tools that will be your trusty companions throughout this project:

Wig Cap: Choose a cap that matches your head size and skin tone for a comfortable and natural fit.
Hair Bundles: Opt for high-quality human hair or synthetic hair bundles in your desired color and texture.
Needle and Thread: A straight, curved needle and strong thread will be your main tools for attaching hair to the cap.
Scissors: A good pair of sharp scissors will help you trim excess lace and hair.
Wig Stand or Mannequin Head: This will provide stability as you work and allow you to style the wig effectively.
Ventilating Needle: If you're creating a lace front wig, a ventilating needle will be necessary for a realistic hairline.

Techniques to Master:

Measuring and Preparing: Learn how to accurately measure your head, mark the hairline, and prepare the cap for wig-making.

Hair Attachment: Grasp how to attach hair bundles to the cap using a needle and thread or specialized wig adhesive.
Customizing the Hairline: Master the technique of creating a natural-looking hairline, whether it's a straight or curved fringe.

Useful Tips for Success:

Patience is Key: Wig-making is a meticulous process that requires patience and practice. Don't rush; take your time to achieve the best results.

Styling and Maintenance: Once your fringe wig is complete, explore styling options and learn how to care for it to keep it looking fabulous.

Get ready to unleash your creativity and transform strands of hair into a work of art that you can proudly wear. Whether you're a beginner or a seasoned DIY enthusiast, this tutorial will equip you with the skills needed to create a stunning fringe wig that's uniquely yours. So, gather your tools, prepare to dive in, and let's get started on your journey to wig-making mastery!

Follow us on instagram @celegant_hair to purchase the tools or book an  appointment if you're in Malaysia

title: What is Fringe Benefits Tax (FBT) and how is FBT calculated?
description:
Fringe benefits tax was introduced in legislation in 1986; prior to this businesses were providing things like cars, corporate boxes and lunches tax-free to employees, their families and executives with very little obligation to make the benefit related to their employment.

The whole purpose of Fringe Benefits Tax legislation is for the government (ATO) to receive the tax that would have been paid, if the employee paid for the benefit out of their own salary from take-home pay. The difference being, FBT is calculated based on the highest tax bracket regardless of what tax bracket an employee is on. Read full article online here. https://www.appliededucation.edu.au/other-news/what-is-fringe-benefits-tax-fbt-and-how-is-fbt-calculated

title: Fringe Benefits Examples
description:
If you're interested in learning more about fringe benefits, then check out our HR Certifications here: https://hr.university/hr-certification-online/

__

Fringe benefits result in better public perception, better brand identity, and market competition for the organization. As for employees, they experience increased happiness, engagement, retention, and motivation. 

Let's explore the most common fringe benefits examples. First, we have bonuses, paid vacations, and athletic club memberships. Other examples include health resort expenses, housing allowance, educational assistance, employee discounts, accident and health benefits, and retirement plans. In addition, we also have group-term life insurance, worker's compensation insurance, unemployment insurance, and family and medical leave. Furthermore, you also need to offer disability insurance. Finally, we have social security and medicare.

title: DIY Genuine leather Fringe crossbody bag | Tandy leather bag | Janis fringe bag
description:
In this video we will finish our Janis fringe bag from Tandy.
This DIY project is a beautiful soft genuine leather fringe bag called Janis. I went to the Tandy leather store the other day to get some leather to make a new bag when I ran across Janis. I didn't see her at first because I was so busy looking at the leather that was on sale and the other DIY kits in the store. After going down several isles, I finally saw her. She was one of the more expensive kits, however I think it was totally worth it for this gorgeous bag. I  plan to go back and get one more DIY kit for sure that I want to make and show you guys. All of the kits were so nice that it was hard to pick one.

If you want one like this it can be purchased from the Tandy Leather store online. 
https://tandyleather.com/collections/kits/products/janis-fringe-bag-kit

Thanks for watching and I'll see you in the next video!
